Since the Grafana instance in AKS relies on the UI rather than the API and is exposed via the NGINX Ingress Controller, Azure API Management (APIM) is not the optimal solution. Below are my recommended alternatives:

Private Internal Load Balancer + Azure Private Endpoint â€“ Provides a highly secure, internal-only access model.

Azure Application Gateway with WAF in Internal Mode â€“ Offers layer-7 routing, security (WAF), and private exposure.

Kubernetes-Native API Gateways â€“ Lightweight, scalable, and better aligned with AKS-native traffic management.

